steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"97f6c","text":"The following general procedures can be used for spills involving small volumes (mL size) of dilute solutions of formaldehyde (e.g.  fixative solution of 4% formaldehyde) contained within a fume hood:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":66,"length":13}],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":131,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"amount","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"amount":"100","error":false,"guid":"04ABCF201A3911EDB67BEDBA3492F246","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"unit":2}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d1hi0","text":"Wear appropriate personal protective equipment(PPE).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"mdp0","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"c8oia","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"6qthr","text":"This should include a reusable respirator if there is not sufficient local area ventilation.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"14gen","text":"Remove any ignition source from the spill area (particularly if the solution has been stabilised with methanol).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"94ctr","text":"If possible, boost ventilation to the area.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"3je44","text":"Absorb any residual solution with absorbent.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"f078c","text":"Clean spill area with detergent and water.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"k2c9","text":"Dry decontaminated spill area with paper towels.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f07ms","text":"Dispose of any absorbent material along with other chemical waste through the university hazardous waste program.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"171nm","text":"If a large volume of concentrated formaldehyde solution is spilled (e.g\u003e  , 37% formaldehyde) or if the spill occurs outside a chemical fume hood or ventilated area, immediately:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":17}],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":73,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"amount","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"amount":"1","error":false,"guid":"56318F601A3911EDB67BEDBA3492F246","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"unit":3}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"cmso0","text":"Alert others working in the area.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"c0aoc","text":"Evacuate the area.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"1ho2u","text":"Restrict the access to the area.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6l4a3","text":"Contact Laboratory Supervisor for use of formaldehyde spills kit containing a urea-based formaldehyde neutralizer (e.g. Spill X-FPTM) which will chemically react with formaldehyde to form a polymer product that is no longer volatile and much less hazardous. These formaldehyde spill neutralizers are commercially available. Locate the spills kit within easy access to where formaldehyde is handled or stored.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a7g47","text":"Formaldehyde is very water soluble and will therefore affect mucous membranes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3i7ip","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"9h8v7","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"9lc6e","text":"Symptoms of acute exposure can result in eye and throat irritation, coughing, wheezing, chest tightness, bronchitis, laryngitis, clouding of the cornea and loss of vision.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"1ior0","text":"The following first aid procedure should be promptly undertaken;","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1vnk9","text":"Exposure via inhalation.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6qpt8","text":"Immediately move the person to fresh air.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8l24u","text":"Contact a first aider and/or refer the person to the University medical center. ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c03l","text":"If the person is having respiratory difficulties, call an ambulance.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"35pvb","text":"Skin or eye exposure:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1knal","text":"Remove contaminated clothing / contact lenses.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9ju4c","text":"Immediately flush with tepid water for at least  .","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":48,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"1eulp","text":"Contact a first aider for assistance.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6mps7","text":"If there is severe irritation, refer to the University medical centre.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"eh9ge","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"duration":900,"guid":"D75EB6801A3911EDB67BEDBA3492F246","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"57r7e","text":"Mix PFA solution with   Buffer A and   Buffer B (recipes below).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":22,"length":1},{"key":1,"offset":37,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"amount","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"amount":"120","error":false,"error_temperature":false,"guid":"AEEDE5B71C7D11ED84CD0A58A9FEAC02","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"temperature":"65","unit":2}},"1":{"type":"amount","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"amount":"380","error":false,"error_temperature":false,"guid":"AEEDE6351C7D11ED84CD0A58A9FEAC02","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"temperature":"65","unit":2}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"53kgc","text":"Filter dissolved PFA using ceramic vacuum filtration system into a conical flask.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1ndqq","text":"Allow solution to cool to  .","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":26,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"9r1ol","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"temperature","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"error_temperature":false,"guid":"EAD105101C7D11EDBE29C9641DB58584","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"temperature":"","unit":32}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"6hor0","text":"Add 1-2 pellets of NaOH to dissolve PFA powder.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4u7ls","text":"Heat solution to   -   on the heat plate with stirrer (use lowest possible heat setting).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":17,"length":1},{"key":1,"offset":21,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"temperature","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"amount":"500","error":false,"error_temperature":false,"guid":"A14705441C7D11ED84CD0A58A9FEAC02","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"temperature":"60","unit":10}},"1":{"type":"temperature","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"amount":"500","error":false,"error_temperature":false,"guid":"A14705A61C7D11ED84CD0A58A9FEAC02","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"temperature":"65","unit":10}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4t3vc","text":"Add to   H2O in beaker with flea.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":7,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"amount","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"amount":"500","error":false,"error_temperature":false,"guid":"9EC044751C7D11ED84CD0A58A9FEAC02","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"temperature":"4","unit":2}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"605hl","text":"Adjust pH solution to 7.4 using 2N HCl. Only use the pH meter designated for PFA preparation.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5ck34","text":"Wash hands with soap and water once finished and before leaving the laboratory.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"84kfb","text":"Label solution according to GHS guidelines.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
